casebody.data:
Milo WILCOX, Appellant, v. DELAWARE RURAL ELECTRIC CO-OPERATIVE, Inc., Appellee. No. 10292. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 5, 1946. H. M. Rust, of Mansfield, Ohio, for appellant. Jones & Kellar, of Delaware, Ohio, and Dargusch, Caren, Greek & King, of Columbus, Ohio, for appellee.

Before SIMONS, MARTIN, aud MILLER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This appeal has been heard and considered on the oral arguments and briefs of attorneys for the parties and the record in the cause; and it appearing that the motion to dismiss made by the defendant (appellee here) was well grounded in law, the judgment of the district court dismissing the amended complaint is affirmed.
